# Rails and Github

###Blog
>     rails new proyect -T --database=postgresql
>     rails db:create
>     rails db:migrate
>     rails g scaffold Blog title:string body:text
>     rails db:migrate
>     localhost:3000/blogs

###Tips
>     rails -h
>     rails db:create |and*2| rails db:migrate
>     git remote -v
>     rake routes | grep porfolio

###Api
>       rails new api --api -T
### Secrets.yml
>     git checkout config/secrets.yml
>     git rm . -r --cached

###Controller -brach
>     git checkout -b controller-generator

###Data view to db html.erb
>     @post.inspect
>     @blog.inspect

### MODEL
>     rails g model Skill title:string percent_utilized:integer

### Rails Console
>       rails c
> Skill.create!(title:"rails",percent_utilized:17)
> Pages/home

### Merge git
>       git merge model-generator
>       git push
>       git checkout -b Resource_generator

### RESOURCES IN RAILS
>       rails g resource Portfoio title:string subtitle:string body: text main_image:text thumb_image:text
>       rails db:migrate
 
###Enum
>     rails g migration add_post_status_to_blogs status:integer
>    blog.rb
>    enum status:draft:0,published:1 }

>     rails c
>     Blog.create!(title:"rails",body:"variado")
>     Blog.last.published! 



 